THE PILOT STATED THAT HE FAILED TO REMOVE THE CONTROL COLUMN GUST LOCK 
PRIOR TO TAKE OFF. IMMEDIATELY AFTER ROTATION, THE AIRCRAFT BEGAN TO 
PORPOISE, DESCENDED UNCONTROLLED, AND LANDED HARD COLLAPSING THE 
LANDING GEAR. HE FURTHER STATED THAT THIS ACCIDENT COULD HAVE BEEN 
PREVENTED BY PERFORMING A THOROUGH PREFLIGHT AND ALSO BY USING A CHECKLIST. 
